<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO W. SAVAGE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec  7 15:19:42 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
There is no futility in presenting thoughts and points of view. There are those who are firm in their convictions and who are not easily swayed. There are those, however, who carefully consider other points of view, and who remain silent or ask further questions. To back off and run when one is not successful in &quot;convincing&quot; a &quot;hard core&quot; opponent is to invalidate your own thoughts and points of view in the eyes of others.<br><br>
Humanity is territorial in space, time, and thought, just like penguins, and other species. This fact cannot be denied. You must work within this framework to be effective in presenting your points.<br><br>
Concerning your comments about PBS, I feel that this page is a public service for which they are to be commended. It is not often that there is a global forum such as this. We need to do more!
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


